snippet.textDisplay:
I have an idea:
What if all streaming companies, big and small, join together in a sort of pact and form one big company to rival Apple and Disney+? Obviously there’s a 00000000000.1 of that happening, but if somehow it DID happen, wouldn’t that be interesting? You could watch most of your favorite TV shows on one single streaming service. Here’s another idea: no bundles, no catches, just a simple huge steaming service that’s maybe $7.99 or $8.99 a month, something in between that. The problem is that it would be like another world war, except with streaming services. Apple, Disney, and the merged companies would be fighting constantly at each other, striving to get more money than the other.
It’s a cool theory though. Plenty of things that can go wrong...plenty of thongs that can go right.

snippet.textDisplay: Yup. Ten years ago I was really excited with the possibility that the cable TV model would go the way of the dinosaur. Unfortunately, we all discovered that the content creators are the ones that dictated the way that cable was setup so naturally when everything went to streaming they would dictate that it continue down the same path. So now we have to pay the same amount of money to subscribe to all the different streaming services in order to watch the shows we want to watch. I've been cancelling my streaming services lately though. I'm sick of all the politics infecting nearly every movie or show produced.
